  "title": "GeoSPARQL geof:buffer() not working according to standard",
  "description": "Hi, this issue is probably related to #803.\nThe following query:\nselect ?o1 ?ret (geof:buffer(?ret, 1, <http://www.opengis.net/def/uom/OGC/1.0/metre>) as ?buf) where {\n\tGRAPH <http://geographica.di.uoa.gr/dataset/clc> {?s1 <http://geo.linkedopendata.gr/corine/ontology#asWKT> ?o1}\n        BIND(geof:boundary(?o1) as ?ret) .\n} limit 1\n\nAs mentioned in #803, incorrectly imports a geo:wktLiteral as internal VSO geometry, but it also has the following 2 issues:\n\nThe ?ret which is the boundary is a string like representation (with no double quotes) with no datatype attached to it. I don't think that geo:wktLiteral datatype is an optional part of the literal and the double quotes should be used.\nWhen ?ret is used as the 1st argument in geof:buffer() I estimate that it is consumed properly but the 2nd and 3rd arguments of geof:buffer(), which represent a radius of 1 meter, are ignored (or a different measure is used) and the POLYGON returned is a vast area with a radius of 100Km around the ?ret geometry. Again the double quotes and the geo:wktLiteral are not used.\n\nBelow is the returned record with ?o1 ?ret and ?buf\n\"POLYGON((21.21482082946 38.604241103633,21.214753050773 38.603677052906,21.214631008421 38.603357774756,21.214286547149 38.602998047923,21.213984128286 38.602709625545,21.213550162213 38.602347764386,21.21321930177 38.601636834862,21.212676466485 38.60128873497,21.212108525495 38.600080513702,21.211724012013 38.599626799668,21.211135920631 38.599289635488,21.210373112725 38.599042731735,21.209583739706 38.599001856303,21.207523580033 38.599497296202,21.206758004654 38.599819434757,21.206552433384 38.600282606399,21.206709654127 38.600848797052,21.207144936549 38.6011755634,21.207993905529 38.601230986309,21.209245164799 38.601282760606,21.210127803879 38.601468115764,21.210595063649 38.602115597762,21.210880595701 38.602738005376,21.211263444472 38.603558739944,21.211644489645 38.604130263358,21.212172047372 38.604388906305,21.21